Be recognized as a technical excellence authority on a specific area/product/technology, both internally and externally to Honeywell. You will assist and manage various teams on differentiated technology roadmap development, leading advanced and strategic products and technologies, governing expert oversight on risk identification and mitigation. You will be a focal point on technical knowledge which you will share with the team and will use to develop strong customer connections. You will promote Honeywell as a world technology leader by external engagements on customerâ€™s symposia, national and international technical conferences and Universities across the globe. 
Key Responsibilities 
Define and lead autonomy technology development supporting aerial vehicle and alternative navigation needs 
Drive VOC with key external and internal customers, leading to the development and transition of key autonomous capabilities 
Drive technology transitions and productization of key autonomy technologies to develop hardware, software, and edge solutions and integrate them onto key manned and unmanned aerial platforms 
Thrive in a fast-paced environment with rapidly changing priorities that require quick adaptation 
YOU MUST HAVE 
Masters in Engineering, Robotics or Computer Science 
Expert in computer vision, Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Machine Learning (ML) as applied to navigation and autonomy for Urban Air Mobility and Unmanned Air Vehicle applications 
Minimum 8 years managing complex technical R&D programs including government customers such as AFRL or DARPA 
WE VALUE 
Ph.D in Aerospace Engineering, Robotics or Computer Science strongly preferred 
Experience deploying complex solutions on unmanned systems for autonomy applications such as automatic landing/takeoff, landmark navigation, visual odometry, optical flow, target tracking or detect and avoid 
Experience with new methods of computer vision including machine learning (especially deep learning) 
Experience working with business leaders to define technology and product roadmaps 
Experience with sensors, perception, dynamics, and autonomous vehicle technology development 
Experience writing DoD proposals, including technical content and develop accurate project cost and resource forecasts 
Drive and motivation for career development 
Team player who can also be independent 
Open to taking on challenges 
Thrives in a fast-paced dynamic environment 
Strong communication and presentation skills 
Ability to work directly with sponsors and customers 
Creativity, technical curiosity and breadth of knowledge 
